Create a plan

**Background:** This project wraps pflag and cobra so that very little of these
libraries are visible or usable on the seam.

## Goal

Create a mechanism to support detecting when updates are available so we can
tell the user.

### Expectations

A new `update` package is created that defines abstractions like:

```go
type BuildInfo struct {
  Version string // The semantic version, or 'snapshot' if not prebuilt
  Source  string // the source (apt, brew, github, etc)
}

type Provider interface {
  LatestVersion(ctx context.Context) (*semver.Version, error)
}

type GitHubProvider struct {
  Owner string `yaml:"owner"`
  Repo  string `yaml:"repo"`
}

type BrewProvider struct {
  Tap  string `yaml:"tap"`
  Name string `yaml:"name"`
}

type CacheProvider struct {
  CacheName    string
  UserCacheDir func() (string, error)
  MkdirAll     func(string) error
  TTL          time.Duration
  Provider     Provider
  // ...
}

// ...

type ProviderRegistry map[string]Provider

func (pr ProviderRegistry) LatestVersion(ctx context.Context, source string) (*semver.Version, error)

type Checker struct {
  build    BuildInfo
  registry *ProviderRegistry
}
```

* `Provider`s return the current version.
* `CacheProvider` wraps `Provider` by storing the "last checked" time and the
  last value discovered in the `os.UserCacheDir()`. This will prevent fetching
  every time. Do not cache errors.
* `ProviderRegistry` supports multiple providers
* `Checker` does the actual checking to decide whether an update exists

On a new version being available, the help menu should add a line to the bottom
saying "a new version is available" and indicate both the current and new
version.

This will require a lot of new wiring, including:

* New `cli.Option` values to pass through the current version and the current
  build source. If the options aren't provided, no update is performed.

* New config values in the YAML for config update sources. This is free-form
  under `update-sources`. Each key under `update-sources` will correspond to the
  key name `source` frm the updater itself, and be assigned to a `yaml` field
  in the source definition. This enables custom `update.Provider`s to be defined
  and configured.

* Add `cli.Option`s for the TTL value for re-checking, and
  `cli.UpateProvider(name, Provider)` for defining custom providers.

  * No providers are used by default. If no providers are specified, the app
    should never check for updates

* New top-level config value for `cache-name` which is the name of the dir in
  the cache (no slashes).
  When unspecified, this becomes just the app name from the root `use`.

Versions are only checked for on `--help` menu, and only displayed on the
`--help` menu. It should have a short/reasonable timeout

We will likely require additional abstractions for testing the update sources.
For GitHub, we will raw network calls on the release API (no library, do not use
`go-github`).

Propose other update sources and how we'll check it.

It's fine that these will not support auth. If someone wants custom auth, they
can overwrite it.

